{"id":"277008846_A_New_Approach_to_the_Study_of_Fixed_Point_Theory_for_Simulation_Functions","abstract":"Let (X, d) be a metric space and T : X → X be a mapping. In this work, we introduce the mapping ζ : [0, ∞) × [0, ∞) → R, called the simulation function and the notion of Z-contraction with respect to ζ which generalize the Banach contraction principle and unify several known types of contractions involving the combination of d(Tx, Ty) and d(x, y). The related fixed point theorems are also proved.","authors":["Farshid Khojasteh","Satish Shukla","Stojan N Radenović"],"meta":["July 2015Filomat 26(6)","DOI:10.2298/FIL1506189K","Project: Approximation Theory"],"references":["270669349_Discussions_on_Recent_Results_for_--Contractive_Mappings","257021918_Comparison_Functions_and_Fixed_Point_Results_in_Partial_Metric_Spaces","244414686_A_Comparison_of_Various_Definitions_of_Contractive_Mappings","243053992_On_Nonlinear_Contractions","306940024_The_solution_by_iteration_of_nonlinear_functional_equation_in_Banach_spaces","256245895_Fixed_point_theorem_for_multivalued_mappings_on_complete_metric_spaces","243450076_Sur_les_Oprations_dans_les_Ensembles_Abstraits_et_leurs_Applications_aux_Equations_Intgrales","243071423_The_solution_by_iteration_of_nonlinear_functional_equations_in_Banach_spaces","242990188_Some_theorems_on_weakly_contractive_maps","220319805_Some_new_common_fixed_point_results_of_generalized_contractive_non-self_multi-valued_mappings"]}